WEBVTT

00:02.152 --> 00:05.258
Christopher's back in town.
He's moving in here with us.

00:05.417 --> 00:08.284
How excited are you to have
a doctor for a roommate?

00:08.286 --> 00:10.787
I think it's time for me
to move back to my own house.

00:10.789 --> 00:13.122
I am having feelings
for Ernesto.

00:13.124 --> 00:15.858
- Are you going back to him?
- I am so sorry.

00:16.756 --> 00:18.795
You come back
here again, I'll kill you!

00:18.797 --> 00:20.296
I've had bad luck with men.

00:20.298 --> 00:21.664
I'm waiting for
the other shoe to drop.

00:21.666 --> 00:23.599
There is no other shoe.

00:23.601 --> 00:25.201
[Cocks gun]

00:25.203 --> 00:27.270
We've been able
to identify the victim.

00:27.272 --> 00:28.538
That's Louie Becker.

00:28.540 --> 00:30.139
What about this man?
He looks dead.

00:30.141 --> 00:31.374
That's my daddy.

00:31.376 --> 00:33.476
You grew up in México.
Didn't you, Katy?

00:33.478 --> 00:36.179
Katy needs a parent!
We can't both go to jail!

00:36.181 --> 00:37.615
- What did you do?
- I'm sorry.

00:37.616 --> 00:38.781
I can't tell you anything else.

00:38.783 --> 00:41.884
- What's wrong?
- [Crying] Michael left me.

00:41.886 --> 00:43.553
Of all the music people
in town,

00:43.555 --> 00:45.688
the only one who wants to
sign me is your wife.

00:45.690 --> 00:48.224
You must be Carmen Luna.

00:48.226 --> 00:49.859
If I'm working with her
and sleeping with you,

00:49.861 --> 00:51.361
she's going to figure it out.

00:51.363 --> 00:53.226
_

00:53.261 --> 00:54.132
_

00:54.199 --> 00:56.332
- You were flirting with her.
- I was just being friendly.

00:56.334 --> 00:58.201
You were flirting.

00:58.203 --> 01:00.303
- If your husband cheats on you...
- Why do I stay?

01:00.305 --> 01:02.638
Women like us...
we don't need men like that.

01:02.640 --> 01:04.340
- Thanks, Carmen.
- Yeah.

01:04.342 --> 01:06.209
From now on,

01:06.211 --> 01:08.344
you can get your jollies
however you please,

01:08.346 --> 01:09.712
but you have to give me
something I want.

01:09.714 --> 01:11.914
- And what's that?
- I want a child.

01:11.916 --> 01:14.650
So, Mrs. Powell,
you'd like to adopt a child.

01:14.652 --> 01:16.185
I'm making a donation.

01:16.187 --> 01:17.920
How much money
are we talking about?

01:17.922 --> 01:19.355
[Pen clicks]

01:20.524 --> 01:22.658
Welcome home, my darling.

01:22.660 --> 01:24.827
[Singsongy] Just
a few more steps. Careful...

01:24.829 --> 01:28.531
For God's sakes, Evelyn.
I'm not an invalid.

01:28.533 --> 01:30.433
Doctor gave me
a clean bill of health.

01:30.435 --> 01:33.436
He also told you
not to exert yourself.

01:33.438 --> 01:35.238
Now I want you to rest.

01:35.240 --> 01:37.573
Let me see to your every need.

01:37.575 --> 01:40.243
Here you are, sweetheart.

01:40.245 --> 01:42.879
Okay.

01:42.881 --> 01:45.248
What's going on here?
What do you mean?

01:45.250 --> 01:47.950
You're being kind.
I find it unsettling.

01:47.952 --> 01:50.720
Like seeing a cat
walking on its hind legs.

01:50.722 --> 01:52.522
Oh, don't be silly.

01:52.524 --> 01:53.756
I've been kind to you
several times in our marriage.

01:53.758 --> 01:55.525
Yes, but I was just
in the hospital

01:55.527 --> 01:57.627
for engaging in sadomasochistic
play with our maid.

01:57.629 --> 01:59.896
Please!
That's all forgotten.

01:59.898 --> 02:03.232
Besides, your little brush
with mortality

02:03.234 --> 02:06.803
just served to remind me
how precious you are to me.

02:06.805 --> 02:08.437
Oh, Evelyn, you must stop.

02:08.440 --> 02:11.407
The hair on my arms
is literally standing on end.

02:11.409 --> 02:13.576
Oh, darling,
I've missed that wit.

02:13.578 --> 02:18.448
Why don't you settle in
while I bring you your present?

02:18.450 --> 02:20.616
- You got me a present?
- Mm-hmm.

02:20.618 --> 02:22.418
Are you trying to butter me up?

02:22.420 --> 02:25.421
I just... wanted to
welcome you home in style.

02:25.423 --> 02:27.890
Now wait here.
I'll be right back.

02:27.892 --> 02:29.659
And the mystery continues.

02:29.661 --> 02:31.928
What did you get me?

02:31.930 --> 02:33.663
Golf clubs?

02:33.665 --> 02:35.731
A new watch?

02:38.569 --> 02:40.803
A small black child?

02:40.805 --> 02:42.839
Adrian, this is Deion,

02:42.841 --> 02:45.541
our new son.

02:51.515 --> 02:55.318
♪

02:55.320 --> 02:58.621
<b>- sync and corrections by Zac -
- www.addic7ed.com -</b>

02:58.623 --> 03:01.424
Sebastien's wife kissed you?

03:01.426 --> 03:03.292
We were just talking
and then... <i>pracata</i>!

03:03.294 --> 03:04.594
She was all over me.

03:04.596 --> 03:05.995
She's in the industry, right?

03:05.997 --> 03:07.663
Those people are always
kissing hello and goodbye.

03:07.665 --> 03:09.298
Not on the lips.

03:09.300 --> 03:11.834
I'm telling you, the way
Jacklyn looked at me,

03:11.836 --> 03:13.469
it meant something to her.

03:13.471 --> 03:14.971
Do you think
she's in love with me?

03:14.973 --> 03:17.039
You think everyone's
in love with you.

03:17.041 --> 03:18.641
Show me.

03:18.643 --> 03:19.876
What?

03:19.878 --> 03:21.477
Show me how she kissed you.

03:21.479 --> 03:23.513
I'm not kissing you.

03:23.515 --> 03:25.448
I'll kiss Rosie.

03:27.518 --> 03:29.318
Okay.

03:29.320 --> 03:31.487
Wow. You really know how
to make a girl feel special.

03:31.489 --> 03:33.456
- Okay, I'm Jacklyn, and you're me.
- Okay.

03:39.463 --> 03:40.830
So what do you think?

03:40.832 --> 03:42.999
I think you have
very soft lips.

03:43.001 --> 03:44.500
Well, I think you smell
really good.

03:44.502 --> 03:47.003
You two need a room?

03:47.005 --> 03:49.839
What does Sebastien think
about all this?

03:49.841 --> 03:52.074
I haven't told him
anything yet.

03:52.076 --> 03:53.509
You know all this time
he's been saying

03:53.511 --> 03:54.810
how his wife is cold and...

03:54.812 --> 03:57.680
Maybe she's cold for a reason.

03:57.682 --> 03:59.515
Or maybe the kiss
meant nothing,

03:59.517 --> 04:01.851
and Sebastien cheats
because he's a cheater.

04:01.853 --> 04:04.487
Well, I can't tell him anything
until I know the truth.

04:04.489 --> 04:06.856
You should talk to Jacklyn.
[Sighs]

04:06.858 --> 04:08.391
Ask her what it meant.

04:08.393 --> 04:10.760
<i>Ay yi yi</i>,
why do I have to be so hot?

04:10.762 --> 04:13.029
[Laughs]

04:14.157 --> 04:16.031
I can't believe
Michael left you.

04:16.034 --> 04:18.034
What happened?

04:18.036 --> 04:20.036
I'm not really sure.

04:20.038 --> 04:22.038
You don't know why he left?

04:22.040 --> 04:23.839
Or maybe he just doesn't like
being married.

04:23.841 --> 04:25.541
I mean, I'm not
the first wife he's left.

04:25.543 --> 04:28.444
Oh. [Huffs] That was
different. Olivia was a nut.

04:28.446 --> 04:29.879
And he left her for you.

04:29.881 --> 04:34.717
Well, I guess we've just...
[Sighs] grown apart.

04:34.719 --> 04:36.586
I'm worried about you.

04:36.588 --> 04:39.388
I mean,
you had that... overdose.

04:39.390 --> 04:41.424
No, I told you,
that was an accident.

04:41.426 --> 04:43.626
Sweetie, what is going on?

04:43.628 --> 04:46.729
You used to tell me everything. I
want us to be close again. [Sighs]

04:46.731 --> 04:48.097
I want that, too.

04:49.800 --> 04:52.435
So, do you think
there's any chance

04:52.437 --> 04:54.403
that Michael might come back?

04:54.405 --> 04:57.573
Marisol, if you really want us
to be better friends,

04:57.575 --> 05:01.077
can you just support me
and stop asking questions?

05:01.079 --> 05:03.913
Of course. Of course.

05:09.753 --> 05:12.154
Now, Deion,
have you read much Dickens?

05:12.156 --> 05:13.756
No, Mrs. Powell.

05:13.758 --> 05:16.425
Well, you are in for a treat.

05:16.427 --> 05:18.995
This one is about

05:18.997 --> 05:22.932
a little orphan boy
named Oliver Twist.

05:22.934 --> 05:24.667
Carmen, would you take Deion
into the kitchen

05:24.669 --> 05:25.968
and make him some lunch?

05:25.970 --> 05:28.771
I need a moment
with Mrs. Powell.

05:28.773 --> 05:30.106
I'm not a nanny.

05:30.108 --> 05:31.574
You're not much of maid,
either.

05:35.512 --> 05:39.515
Evelyn, when you told me
you wanted a child,

05:39.517 --> 05:42.618
I assumed
we'd discuss the idea.

05:42.620 --> 05:44.120
You thought you could
talk me out of it.

05:44.122 --> 05:46.622
How in the world did you
get a child so quickly?

05:46.624 --> 05:48.958
I simply filled out
the application...

05:48.960 --> 05:51.594
and then I donated
a small building.

05:51.596 --> 05:53.629
You bribed your way
into this adoption.

05:53.631 --> 05:56.465
We haven't actually
adopted Deion yet.

05:56.467 --> 05:57.700
We're fostering him.

05:57.702 --> 06:00.002
It's more of
a lease-to-buy situation,

06:00.004 --> 06:01.771
like with your Lexus.

06:01.773 --> 06:03.873
So he's not permanent?
We can still change our minds?

06:03.875 --> 06:05.775
Are you uncomfortable with
a child of color?

06:05.777 --> 06:07.810
Of course not!
I don't want any child.

06:07.812 --> 06:10.212
We are far too old
to start over with all of this.

06:10.214 --> 06:13.215
Listen, you can just leave
the child-rearing to me.

06:13.217 --> 06:15.651
You can focus on
selling this house.

06:15.653 --> 06:17.687
- We're still on that?
- Yes, we're still on that.

06:17.689 --> 06:19.955
We're starting a new chapter
in our lives.

06:19.957 --> 06:22.124
A change of scenery would
do us all good.

06:22.126 --> 06:23.859
Fine.
I'll talk to the realtor.

06:23.861 --> 06:27.029
Don't look so grim!
We're doing a wonderful thing.

06:27.031 --> 06:28.898
With the right education
and opportunities,

06:28.900 --> 06:31.167
Deion could become
the next Barack Obama.

06:31.169 --> 06:33.836
Bite your tongue!

06:36.907 --> 06:39.508
[Humming]

06:39.510 --> 06:41.510
Mmm!

06:41.512 --> 06:44.680
[Continues humming]

06:46.717 --> 06:48.250
[Groans]

06:48.252 --> 06:49.852
[Utensil clatters] [Sighs]

06:49.854 --> 06:51.954
[Slams drawer]

06:53.523 --> 06:56.025
[Opens drawer]

06:56.027 --> 06:58.694
Dr. Neff, have you been
rearranging the kitchen?

06:58.696 --> 07:01.163
Well, doesn't this setup
make so much more sense?

07:01.165 --> 07:03.032
Not really,
I can't find anything.

07:03.034 --> 07:04.667
Where's my soup ladle?

07:04.669 --> 07:07.536
[Opens drawer]

07:07.538 --> 07:09.038
<i>Voilá, Zoilá.</i>

07:09.040 --> 07:12.041
That does not rhyme.
Why did you do this?

07:12.043 --> 07:15.711
Because I'm a surgeon, and I
like my instruments just so.

07:15.713 --> 07:17.246
Everything in its place.

07:17.248 --> 07:19.215
Everything was in its place...
the places I like.

07:19.217 --> 07:21.584
And...

07:21.586 --> 07:22.918
what is this?

07:22.920 --> 07:26.255
That is hospital-grade
antibacterial cleanser.

07:26.257 --> 07:28.858
So that's why the kitchen
smells like bleach?

07:28.860 --> 07:30.893
You've been recleaning
after I clean?

07:30.895 --> 07:32.728
With that, you could perform
open heart surgery

07:32.730 --> 07:34.196
right here on this counter.

07:34.198 --> 07:37.066
No, I can't. I don't know
where the knives are.

07:37.068 --> 07:39.935
Listen, I have a whole system
of doing this,

07:39.937 --> 07:42.571
so please don't mess
with my kitchen.

07:42.573 --> 07:44.807
That's funny. I thought this was
Genevieve's kitchen.

07:44.809 --> 07:46.709
And I work for Genevieve.

07:46.711 --> 07:49.111
Well, now that I live here,
you work for both of us.

07:49.113 --> 07:51.647
That was not my understanding.

07:51.649 --> 07:53.916
Well, then...

07:53.918 --> 07:57.086
I'm glad we cleared things up.

08:00.924 --> 08:03.225
Okay, <i>papito</i>,
let's play a game.

08:03.227 --> 08:06.328
I'll give you 5 points
if you make your bed.

08:06.330 --> 08:07.997
Try $5.

08:07.999 --> 08:09.598
[Knock on door]

08:09.600 --> 08:12.601
Hi, uh, Rosie, do...
do you have a moment?

08:12.603 --> 08:14.003
Of course.

08:14.005 --> 08:15.604
Go play with Katy.

08:15.606 --> 08:17.807
So I'm not getting the $5?

08:17.809 --> 08:20.075
- <i>Ândale</i>.
- Mm.

08:20.077 --> 08:21.911
[Chuckles]

08:21.913 --> 08:25.614
So now that Michael's, uh...
not here,

08:25.616 --> 08:28.150
I was hoping you could
help out more with babysitting.

08:28.152 --> 08:30.953
Oh, it would be my pleasure.

08:30.955 --> 08:32.621
How are you feeling?

08:32.623 --> 08:34.789
Uh, it's hard,

08:34.792 --> 08:37.126
but I'm trying to stay strong
for Katy.

08:37.128 --> 08:38.961
She likes you, you know.

08:38.962 --> 08:42.331
Since you started here, she
talks more and she smiles more.

08:42.332 --> 08:44.099
I'm so glad.

08:44.101 --> 08:46.168
And Miguel is so sweet,
always wanting to play with her.

08:46.170 --> 08:48.304
[Chuckles] It's nice that Katy
has a friend her own age.

08:48.306 --> 08:50.906
Yes, Miguel is a...

08:52.142 --> 08:53.876
Good boy.

08:53.878 --> 08:55.945
Yeah, you did
a wonderful job raising him.

08:55.947 --> 08:58.647
He's an absolute angel.

08:58.649 --> 08:59.982
Mm-hmm.

08:59.984 --> 09:02.084
- Thanks again, Rosie.
- Mm.

09:07.023 --> 09:11.794
<i>Ay, Virgen María...</i>

09:11.796 --> 09:13.062
[Knock on door]

09:13.064 --> 09:14.663
Jacklyn.
Do you have a second?

09:14.665 --> 09:16.165
Of course. Come in.

09:16.167 --> 09:18.367
Come in. What's up?

09:18.369 --> 09:20.870
Okay, I wanted to
ask you something,

09:20.872 --> 09:24.173
- but it's kind of personal.
- Ooh.

09:24.175 --> 09:25.708
Sorry to interrupt.

09:25.710 --> 09:27.176
You wanted to see that artwork
when it came in?

09:27.178 --> 09:28.410
Oh, yes, yes.

09:28.412 --> 09:30.713
Oh, that's perfect,
just like you.

09:30.715 --> 09:32.715
[Giggles] Thank you, James.

09:32.717 --> 09:34.350
[Chuckles]

09:36.086 --> 09:38.687
Sorry about that.
You were saying?

09:38.689 --> 09:40.856
You know what? Never mind.

09:40.858 --> 09:43.692
Carmen, you can't say you want
to ask me something personal

09:43.694 --> 09:44.894
and then drop it.

09:44.896 --> 09:47.329
Okay.
[Chuckles]

09:47.331 --> 09:48.898
Well...

09:48.900 --> 09:52.234
the last time I was in here,
you... kissed me.

09:52.236 --> 09:53.936
And I was wondering
if that meant

09:53.938 --> 09:55.404
that you were a little bit...

09:55.406 --> 09:58.374
- Mm...
- Gay?

09:58.376 --> 10:00.776
- Oh. Uh...
- But now I see you kiss everybody,

10:00.778 --> 10:02.077
so clearly, you know,
you're not.

10:02.079 --> 10:03.879
Of course I'm not gay.
[Chuckles]

10:03.881 --> 10:05.714
I'm married... to a man.

10:05.716 --> 10:08.384
I know. I'm sorry.
It's just that...

10:08.386 --> 10:11.453
The way you kissed me, I...

10:11.455 --> 10:13.022
[Sighs] Oh.

10:13.024 --> 10:15.257
I thought that we had
a moment. [Chuckles]

10:15.259 --> 10:17.726
[Stammers] Wait.

10:17.728 --> 10:20.095
I...

10:20.097 --> 10:23.065
I had no idea you felt
the same way. Huh?

10:23.067 --> 10:25.267
Carmen... [Sighs]

10:25.269 --> 10:27.736
I can't stop thinking
about that kiss either.

10:27.738 --> 10:30.072
I... I'm confused.
You just said you're not gay.

10:30.074 --> 10:32.074
I'm not!
And neither are you, right?

10:32.076 --> 10:33.909
Right.

10:33.911 --> 10:38.147
We're just two curious women
who shared a special connection.

10:38.149 --> 10:39.748
And maybe...

10:39.750 --> 10:44.119
we're finally ready to...
explore that connection.

10:48.200 --> 10:49.750
Michael, it's Marisol.

10:49.785 --> 10:51.686
Taylor told me
what's been going on,

10:51.721 --> 10:53.798
and I just feel
so awful about it.

10:53.901 --> 10:56.868
[TV playing indistinctly]
<i>Yes! Come on! Kill him!</i>

10:56.870 --> 10:59.538
Anyway, I was hoping
I could talk to you.

10:59.540 --> 11:01.773
Call me, please.
[Beep]

11:01.775 --> 11:04.910
You got him! Take him out!

11:04.912 --> 11:06.678
Jesse.

11:06.680 --> 11:09.548
Oh! Oh, uh,
was I being too loud?

11:09.550 --> 11:11.216
No, no.

11:11.218 --> 11:14.453
I think it's sexy when you get
excited about sports.

11:14.455 --> 11:16.721
Really? You should see me
watch football.

11:16.723 --> 11:18.790
I'd knock your socks off.
[Chuckles]

11:18.792 --> 11:20.592
Well, I'll...
I'll leave you alone.

11:20.594 --> 11:22.594
I don't want to distract you
from your job hunt.

11:22.596 --> 11:25.397
Oh, stay.
I'm... I'm on a break.

11:25.399 --> 11:27.566
I can see that.

11:27.568 --> 11:29.901
You know what we should do?

11:29.903 --> 11:32.938
Is go upstairs and put on
some music...

11:32.940 --> 11:34.739
Mm-hmm.
[Chuckles]

11:34.741 --> 11:36.408
Light some candles...
Mm.

11:36.410 --> 11:40.745
And then polish... your...
[Whispers] <i>résumé</i>.

11:40.747 --> 11:43.582
See, I was with you...
[Chuckles]

11:43.584 --> 11:45.917
Right up until the end there.

11:45.919 --> 11:49.254
Come on, I love
helping people find work.

11:49.256 --> 11:50.755
It really turns me on.

11:50.757 --> 11:53.291
[Chuckles]
No, my <i>résumé</i>'s good.

11:53.293 --> 11:55.660
I'm just waiting to hear back
on a few leads.

11:55.662 --> 11:57.796
I could reach out
to my contacts,

11:57.798 --> 11:59.731
help you get a few meetings.

11:59.733 --> 12:03.301
Marisol, we agreed not to mix
business with pleasure.

12:03.303 --> 12:05.570
All right?
You have to trust me.

12:05.572 --> 12:07.405
I'll find a job eventually.

12:07.407 --> 12:09.741
Of course you will.

12:09.743 --> 12:11.443
I believe in you.

12:16.782 --> 12:19.951
♪

12:25.625 --> 12:27.459
Jacklyn said she has
the hots for you?

12:27.461 --> 12:28.627
Mm-hmm.

12:28.629 --> 12:29.961
What'd you say?

12:29.963 --> 12:31.863
I made up an excuse
and ran out.

12:31.865 --> 12:34.666
<i>Mon dieu</i>.
Jacklyn is a lesbian.

12:34.668 --> 12:35.967
Are you okay?

12:35.969 --> 12:37.369
It explains a lot,

12:37.371 --> 12:39.671
like why she thinks
I'm bad in bed.

12:39.673 --> 12:41.673
<i>Papi</i>, you're amazing in bed.

12:41.675 --> 12:43.708
I know! Look at me.

12:43.710 --> 12:45.310
[Cell phone chimes and buzzes]
Oh.

12:47.780 --> 12:50.649
It's Jacklyn. She wants me to
meet her Friday night.

12:50.651 --> 12:52.551
[Scoffs] She knows I will
be home late on Friday.

12:52.553 --> 12:53.818
She's making a move.

12:53.820 --> 12:56.488
Oh, my God.
What do I tell her?

12:56.490 --> 12:58.056
Tell her you're in.

12:58.058 --> 12:59.824
What?

12:59.826 --> 13:02.027
You two have some drinks.
She'll hit on you.

13:02.029 --> 13:03.895
I will come home
at exactly 8:00,

13:03.897 --> 13:05.630
and catch you two in the act.

13:05.632 --> 13:09.334
[Chuckles] Sebastien, we are
not having a threeway.

13:09.336 --> 13:11.836
No, if she's with you,
she breaks our prenup.

13:11.838 --> 13:14.573
I can leave her without losing
any of my money.

13:14.575 --> 13:16.007
You wanna trick your wife?

13:16.009 --> 13:20.845
Carmen, she's been tricking me
our whole marriage.

13:20.847 --> 13:22.547
What are you doing?

13:24.350 --> 13:26.685
<i>Zãngano</i>! You told her "yes"?

13:26.687 --> 13:28.353
Please,
you have to do this, okay?

13:28.355 --> 13:30.355
So I can leave her
and we can be together.

13:30.357 --> 13:33.058
Don't you want that?

13:33.060 --> 13:35.026
Fine.

13:35.028 --> 13:38.897
I'll seduce your wife,
but I won't enjoy it.

13:38.899 --> 13:42.434
Genevieve, I've got a problem.

13:42.436 --> 13:44.703
Is this about
your pregnancy mustache?

13:44.705 --> 13:46.938
I think I have
a concealer somewhere.

13:46.940 --> 13:49.841
What?
No, that's not my problem.

13:49.843 --> 13:52.110
- If you say so.
- It's Dr. Neff.

13:52.112 --> 13:54.379
He keeps doing my housework
behind my back,

13:54.381 --> 13:55.714
rearranging the kitchen.

13:55.716 --> 13:58.049
- Really?
- Yeah, and it's rude.

13:58.051 --> 14:01.119
I don't go to the hospital
and reoperate on his patients.

14:01.121 --> 14:03.722
But why not
just accept the help?

14:03.724 --> 14:06.691
You're not exactly
at your best right now.

14:06.693 --> 14:08.693
Not at my best?

14:08.695 --> 14:11.563
Oh, my God.
You're taking his side.

14:11.565 --> 14:14.032
You're pregnant.

14:14.034 --> 14:17.702
It's understandable that
you'd be... slipping a little.

14:17.704 --> 14:19.404
I can't believe this.

14:19.406 --> 14:21.806
You're saying I'm bad
at my job.

14:22.127 --> 14:24.394
No!
I would never say that.

14:24.396 --> 14:25.796
Thank you.

14:25.798 --> 14:28.398
You know where I sleep.

14:33.538 --> 14:35.839
[Footsteps approaching]
Coming!

14:38.042 --> 14:39.610
<i>Santo Dios!</i>

14:39.612 --> 14:42.045
You joined the priesthood
because of me?

14:42.047 --> 14:45.883
What? Oh! No, it's...
it's for an audition.

14:45.885 --> 14:47.084
Come in.

14:47.086 --> 14:48.852
Oh.

14:48.854 --> 14:51.094
I thought maybe
you were so sad

14:51.129 --> 14:54.317
from our breakup, you...

14:54.693 --> 14:57.694
Became a priest? No.
[Chuckles]

14:57.696 --> 15:00.964
I've just, uh, I'm just trying
to go on more auditions.

15:00.966 --> 15:02.699
I booked a big commercial.

15:02.701 --> 15:04.635
Oh? It sounds like
you're doing great.

15:04.637 --> 15:06.703
Yeah, I'm... I'm going
to the gym a lot,

15:06.705 --> 15:08.305
eating healthy,
going to meetings.

15:08.307 --> 15:10.107
I haven't had a drink
in forever.

15:10.109 --> 15:11.708
That's wonderful.

15:11.710 --> 15:15.078
I was worried you might
fall off the wagon.

15:15.080 --> 15:17.214
But you didn't!

15:17.216 --> 15:19.650
How's Ernesto?

15:19.852 --> 15:21.818
Good.

15:21.820 --> 15:26.456
Yeah, um, he had to go back
to México for a little bit.

15:26.458 --> 15:28.792
That's actually why I'm here.

15:28.794 --> 15:31.294
I think Miguel needs
to talk to a man.

15:31.296 --> 15:33.163
I-I...

15:33.165 --> 15:34.965
found this in his bed.

15:34.967 --> 15:36.967
[Laughs]

15:36.969 --> 15:39.002
What, hasn't he heard of
the Internet?

15:39.004 --> 15:40.971
Spence, he's a little boy.

15:40.973 --> 15:45.208
I don't wanna embarrass him,
but you've got to talk to him,

15:45.210 --> 15:46.443
give him some man advice.

15:46.445 --> 15:48.011
Like what?

15:48.013 --> 15:50.380
Like he needs to respect women
for their brains

15:50.382 --> 15:52.482
- and not their boobies.
- Okay.

15:52.484 --> 15:54.351
And don't hide pornos
in your bed

15:54.353 --> 15:56.319
where your mother could
find them.

15:56.321 --> 15:57.821
Got it.

15:59.557 --> 16:01.158
Thank you.

16:02.326 --> 16:05.962
I'm so glad you're still
in Miguel's life.

16:05.964 --> 16:10.867
I've... got to get to
this audition.

16:10.869 --> 16:13.837
[Exhales]

16:13.839 --> 16:15.172
Goodbye, Spence.

16:21.546 --> 16:23.213
[Door closes]

16:30.855 --> 16:33.056
I appreciate
your agreeing to see me.

16:33.058 --> 16:34.925
I know we've had our issues.

16:34.927 --> 16:36.993
Of course.
Water under the bridge.

16:36.995 --> 16:38.361
[Inhales sharply]

16:38.363 --> 16:42.933
You look... terrible,
by the way.

16:42.935 --> 16:45.335
We recently took in
a foster son.

16:45.337 --> 16:46.536
[Squeaks]

16:46.538 --> 16:48.038
Mrs. Powell mentioned that.

16:48.040 --> 16:49.506
Now the halls in my home
are filled

16:49.508 --> 16:51.408
with the laughter of a child.

16:51.410 --> 16:54.044
It's a nightmare.

16:54.046 --> 16:55.879
So where are we
on selling the house?

16:55.881 --> 16:57.547
Evelyn's impatient.

16:57.549 --> 16:59.583
[Sighs]
I'm doing everything I can.

16:59.585 --> 17:02.886
What if I knocked a million
or two off the asking price?

17:02.888 --> 17:05.555
The problem is not the price.
It's the disclosures.

17:05.557 --> 17:08.191
Your home has been
the site of a murder,

17:08.193 --> 17:10.359
a suicide,
and a chopped off leg.

17:10.362 --> 17:14.064
Well, we don't have to
tell people about that.

17:14.066 --> 17:16.031
Oh, yes, we do.
It's the law.

17:16.034 --> 17:19.935
When people hear stories about
this house, they run screaming.

17:19.938 --> 17:23.140
Really?

17:23.142 --> 17:25.308
That's too bad.

17:25.310 --> 17:27.410
Then why are you smiling?

17:27.412 --> 17:31.948
Sebastien, you've given me
an absolutely terrible idea.

17:34.252 --> 17:36.153
Now how can I help you,
Ms. Suarez?

17:36.155 --> 17:38.455
Well, I heard the country club
was hiring.

17:38.457 --> 17:40.490
Wonderful.
Is that your résumé?

17:40.492 --> 17:42.926
Actually, the job isn't for me.
I run a placement agency,

17:42.928 --> 17:44.494
and I have an excellent
candidate for you.

17:44.496 --> 17:48.098
He's hardworking,
detail-oriented.

17:48.100 --> 17:51.067
- Sounds promising.
- His name is Jesse Morgan.

17:52.470 --> 17:53.937
Oh.

17:53.939 --> 17:55.672
No. No.

17:55.674 --> 17:57.274
I'm not about
to hire him again.

17:57.276 --> 17:59.976
Again? He worked here
a few months ago.

17:59.978 --> 18:02.279
I'm sorry. I didn't see that
on his résumé.

18:02.281 --> 18:05.282
I'm sure he'd rather not
call attention to getting fired.

18:07.318 --> 18:11.121
Another employee reported him
for violating club rules.

18:11.123 --> 18:14.090
What did Jesse do?

18:14.092 --> 18:15.525
I'm not at liberty to say.

18:15.527 --> 18:17.694
Maybe there was some
sort of misunderstanding.

18:17.696 --> 18:19.629
May I speak to
the other employee?

18:19.631 --> 18:24.534
I'm sorry.
He... died recently.

18:24.536 --> 18:26.636
You probably heard about it
in the news.

18:26.638 --> 18:28.438
The tennis pro
who was murdered?

18:28.440 --> 18:29.673
[Scoffs]

18:29.675 --> 18:33.210
Jesse had an incident
with Louie Becker?

18:33.212 --> 18:36.079
Yes. It was very unpleasant.

18:37.648 --> 18:40.517
If I were you, I'd stay away
from Jesse Morgan.

18:40.519 --> 18:44.187
♪

18:46.018 --> 18:50.761
So Dr. Neff goes behind my back,
starts redoing all my housework.

18:50.859 --> 18:53.026
So he does your work,
and you're complaining?

18:53.028 --> 18:56.863
I take pride in my work.
Who's the best maid you know?

18:58.832 --> 19:00.700
The answer is me!

19:00.702 --> 19:02.869
I think I'm very good.

19:02.871 --> 19:04.837
Well, I stink, so at least
you're not the worst.

19:04.839 --> 19:06.306
Tomorrow,
you know what I'm gonna do?

19:06.308 --> 19:08.174
When Genevieve are Dr. Neff
are playing tennis,

19:08.176 --> 19:09.876
I'm gonna scrub
every inch of that house.

19:09.878 --> 19:11.210
On your day off?

19:11.212 --> 19:13.112
Girl, you need a hobby.

19:13.114 --> 19:15.782
Oh, sorry I'm late.
I'm having a day.

19:15.784 --> 19:17.383
What is it?

19:17.385 --> 19:20.353
I was trying to help Jesse
get a job at the country club.

19:20.355 --> 19:22.255
Turns out he already
worked there.

19:22.257 --> 19:24.123
He was fired a few months ago.

19:24.125 --> 19:27.060
So? I get fired all the time.
[Chuckles]

19:27.062 --> 19:29.195
You should be
less proud of that.

19:29.197 --> 19:30.463
There's more.

19:30.465 --> 19:32.899
Louie Becker was the one
who got him fired.

19:32.901 --> 19:35.134
Jesse knew the guy
who got murdered?

19:35.136 --> 19:36.903
Apparently, but he never
mentioned it to me.

19:36.905 --> 19:40.073
Wait. Wasn't Jesse the one
who found Louie's hand?

19:40.075 --> 19:41.307
That's suspicious.

19:41.309 --> 19:43.409
But I think it's just
a coincidence.

19:43.411 --> 19:45.311
Maybe not.
What if he planted it?

19:45.313 --> 19:47.146
What are you guys saying?

19:47.148 --> 19:49.949
Maybe Jesse saw something
in the war,

19:49.951 --> 19:54.320
and he went crazy, and now
he's got the <i>pre-STDs</i>.

19:54.322 --> 19:57.924
It's PTSD, sweetie.
But Rosie has a point.

19:57.926 --> 19:59.425
How much do you really know
about Jesse?

19:59.427 --> 20:02.261
I guess not a lot.

20:02.263 --> 20:04.097
Well, you know
he can be violent,

20:04.099 --> 20:06.933
like when he attacked that guy
and threw him out of your house.

20:06.935 --> 20:08.167
Mm-hmm.

20:08.169 --> 20:10.069
Come on, we're talking
about Jesse.

20:10.071 --> 20:12.005
My Jesse.

20:12.007 --> 20:15.441
Look, we all agree
that Blanca didn't kill Louie.

20:15.443 --> 20:18.945
You've got to find out
if it was really Jesse.

20:18.947 --> 20:21.414
- I'm not a detective.
- That never stopped you before.

20:21.416 --> 20:22.982
You wrote a whole book

20:22.984 --> 20:24.317
about snooping around
other people's houses.

20:24.319 --> 20:25.818
Just Marisol his ass.

20:25.820 --> 20:27.520
[Laughter] [Exhales]

20:32.126 --> 20:34.961
[Children shouting playfully]

20:34.963 --> 20:37.330
So where'd you get this?

20:37.332 --> 20:40.967
It's okay.
You're not in trouble.

20:40.969 --> 20:42.268
My friend TJ.

20:42.270 --> 20:44.103
He steals them
from his brother.

20:44.105 --> 20:47.306
Yeah, I had a friend like that.

20:47.308 --> 20:48.474
Adam Gallico.

20:48.476 --> 20:50.877
He used to share
his dirty magazines.

20:50.879 --> 20:52.378
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

20:52.380 --> 20:56.182
But I was a teenager.
You're too young for this stuff.

20:56.184 --> 21:00.186
And women are not objects.
It's good to remember that.

21:00.188 --> 21:01.454
Okay.

21:01.456 --> 21:03.156
Hey, I know this is
embarrassing,

21:03.158 --> 21:07.293
but it's normal to be
interested in this stuff.

21:07.295 --> 21:11.164
And anytime you wanna talk
about guy stuff, I'm here.

21:11.166 --> 21:14.167
How do you get a girl
to like you?

21:14.169 --> 21:16.169
[Both laugh]

21:16.171 --> 21:18.004
Do you have a crush on someone?

21:18.006 --> 21:20.840
Maybe.

21:20.842 --> 21:22.842
Ah, well, you gotta
talk to her.

21:22.844 --> 21:24.077
Tell her how you feel.

21:24.079 --> 21:26.212
Can't expect her
to read your mind.

21:26.214 --> 21:28.214
Do you miss mom?

21:28.216 --> 21:31.150
I do. A lot.

21:31.152 --> 21:32.552
You should tell her
how you feel.

21:32.554 --> 21:34.020
She can't read your mind.

21:34.022 --> 21:37.890
Hey, that's my advice, okay?

21:39.093 --> 21:40.493
[Exhales]

21:43.897 --> 21:45.264
Deion, my boy.

21:46.567 --> 21:48.234
[Under breath] Words
I'd never thought I'd say.

21:48.236 --> 21:49.869
[Normal voice]
How you getting along?

21:49.871 --> 21:53.039
- Good, Mr. Powell.
- Wonderful.

21:53.041 --> 21:55.208
[Sighs]

21:55.210 --> 21:57.043
I want you to be happy here.

21:57.045 --> 22:01.214
And I don't want you to worry
about any of the bad things

22:01.216 --> 22:03.249
you might've heard
about the house.

22:03.251 --> 22:04.617
What bad things?

22:04.619 --> 22:07.186
You know, the maid
who got murdered here.

22:07.188 --> 22:10.356
Oh, but you're too old
to believe in ghosts.

22:10.358 --> 22:13.025
[Chuckles nervously]
She's a... she's a ghost?

22:13.027 --> 22:15.394
Well, I don't know if "ghost"
is the right word.

22:15.396 --> 22:19.098
Maybe "shadow figure"?
Maybe "demon"?

22:19.100 --> 22:22.568
Anyway, sweet dreams.

22:22.570 --> 22:24.403
[Switch clicks]

22:26.406 --> 22:28.908
[Switch clicks]
Something wrong?

22:28.910 --> 22:30.576
I just want the light on.

22:30.578 --> 22:33.579
Oh, dear, I've scared you.
Well, it's just a story.

22:33.581 --> 22:35.248
You're perfectly safe here.

22:35.250 --> 22:37.450
- Okay.
- Although...

22:37.452 --> 22:40.653
I guess I should warn you
about the...

22:40.655 --> 22:43.256
chopped off leg.

22:43.258 --> 22:45.424
You heard about that, right?

22:48.962 --> 22:52.598
♪

22:54.000 --> 23:00.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

23:05.612 --> 23:07.980
Who the hell are you?

23:07.982 --> 23:10.183
I'm the maid.

23:10.185 --> 23:11.584
Who are you?

23:15.329 --> 23:18.025
[Singsongy] Wake up,
my little sleepyhead.

23:19.179 --> 23:20.679
Deion?

23:20.681 --> 23:23.348
[Muffled crying]

23:23.350 --> 23:25.717
Sweetheart?

23:28.988 --> 23:30.755
What's wrong?

23:30.757 --> 23:32.857
I don't wanna
live here anymore.

23:35.695 --> 23:40.695
[Laughs] You are quite
the tennis player, my love.

23:40.701 --> 23:43.034
It's a miracle I could
play at all,

23:43.036 --> 23:46.371
considering how fetching you are
in your tennis whites.

23:46.373 --> 23:48.340
[Loudly] Ahem.

23:48.342 --> 23:50.375
Zoila!

23:50.377 --> 23:51.910
Joy.

23:51.912 --> 23:54.212
What's going on here?

23:54.214 --> 23:56.448
We should ask you
the same thing.

23:56.450 --> 23:58.950
Joy used to be Dr. Neff's maid.

23:58.952 --> 24:01.386
He hired her behind your back.

24:03.055 --> 24:06.157
Well, aren't you gonna
say something?

24:07.393 --> 24:09.227
Bad Christopher.

24:09.229 --> 24:11.296
Well, you were the one who said
that if Joy came

24:11.298 --> 24:13.898
on Zoila's day off, they'd never
find out about each other.

24:13.900 --> 24:17.202
Oh, my God.
You were in on this?

24:17.204 --> 24:18.903
You have to understand.

24:18.905 --> 24:20.772
Christopher's very loyal,

24:20.774 --> 24:23.775
and Joy's been his housekeeper
for years.

24:23.777 --> 24:26.745
Upstairs. Now!

24:31.984 --> 24:33.318
Mmm.

24:33.320 --> 24:36.388
What was that for?

24:36.390 --> 24:39.124
In case I don't make it back.

24:42.094 --> 24:43.461
You have another maid.

24:43.463 --> 24:46.264
But Joy means nothing to me,
I swear.

24:46.266 --> 24:48.266
We've been together
for 20 years.

24:48.268 --> 24:50.301
Doesn't that mean
anything to you?

24:50.303 --> 24:52.270
You have to understand,
I have needs.

24:52.272 --> 24:54.406
[Exhales deeply]
Cleaning needs.

24:54.408 --> 24:56.941
So I'm not enough for you
anymore, is that it?

24:56.943 --> 24:59.978
Joy gets the job done,
that's all.

24:59.980 --> 25:03.515
And the truth is, you need help
while you're pregnant.

25:03.517 --> 25:05.283
You can't clean
this big house alone.

25:05.285 --> 25:06.985
You should've talked to me
about it

25:06.987 --> 25:08.920
instead of sneaking around
behind my back.

25:08.922 --> 25:12.957
I tried, but you always get
so defensive.

25:12.959 --> 25:14.826
I do not!

25:14.828 --> 25:16.361
Okay, I hear it.

25:16.363 --> 25:19.769
Honey,
you are twice the size

25:19.770 --> 25:22.267
but only half the maid.

25:22.269 --> 25:26.271
And this one can't help out
for at least 10 years.

25:26.273 --> 25:28.540
This is
Dr. Neff's influence.

25:28.542 --> 25:30.508
He put these thoughts
in your head.

25:30.510 --> 25:32.444
- That's not fair.
- I don't like him.

25:32.446 --> 25:34.446
Well, I do,

25:34.448 --> 25:38.116
and I may not have
that many chances left.

25:38.118 --> 25:42.020
Please, I need you to help me
make this work.

25:42.022 --> 25:46.324
This is just temporary
until you have the baby.

25:46.326 --> 25:49.394
Then things will go back
to the way they were.

25:49.396 --> 25:51.996
So you're not replacing me?

25:51.998 --> 25:54.566
I couldn't if I tried.

25:59.716 --> 26:02.841
I know what you did,
you son of a bitch!

26:02.843 --> 26:05.977
You know, you start a lot
of conversations that way.

26:05.979 --> 26:08.546
Deion wants to go back
to the group home.

26:08.548 --> 26:10.849
He asked me to call him a cab.

26:10.851 --> 26:12.183
That's ridiculous.

26:12.185 --> 26:14.018
I'll spring for a town car.

26:14.020 --> 26:15.320
This isn't funny!

26:15.322 --> 26:17.856
I spent the last two hours
convincing Deion

26:17.858 --> 26:19.324
this isn't a haunted house.

26:19.326 --> 26:21.559
Adrian, how could you?!
He is just a child.

26:21.561 --> 26:23.528
Legally, we have to disclose
those things to home buyers.

26:23.530 --> 26:27.031
I thought Deion deserved
the same courtesy.

26:27.033 --> 26:30.001
For God's sake,
he is your foster son.

26:30.003 --> 26:31.569
I agree to disagree.

26:31.571 --> 26:33.538
This attitude is so unbecoming.
He is a wonderful boy!

26:33.540 --> 26:36.374
If you could just open up
your heart just the tiniest bit!

26:36.376 --> 26:38.009
- No!
- Why not?

26:38.011 --> 26:39.244
Because I don't want to
get attached again.

26:41.347 --> 26:44.215
I already had a son.

26:44.217 --> 26:46.417
[Sighs] [Whispers] Adrian.

26:46.419 --> 26:48.419
Barrett was everything to me.

26:48.421 --> 26:51.589
I gave him all the love I had,
and then he was gone.

26:52.290 --> 26:57.262
So forgive me if I can't
go through that again.

26:57.264 --> 27:00.265
[Sighs] Look...

27:02.134 --> 27:04.903
I miss Barrett, too,

27:04.905 --> 27:07.972
every moment of every day.

27:07.974 --> 27:12.577
But I don't want his legacy
to be endless misery.

27:12.579 --> 27:17.115
He wouldn't have
wanted that for us.

27:17.117 --> 27:19.250
It's time to move forward.

27:19.686 --> 27:24.255
Now Deion is joining
this family.

27:24.534 --> 27:26.133
You can either...

27:26.502 --> 27:29.863
be a part of it or not.

27:31.497 --> 27:34.265
It's entirely up to you.

27:34.267 --> 27:37.302
[Sighs]

27:42.902 --> 27:47.846
Okay, <i>señor y señorita</i>,
I am making lunch.

27:47.948 --> 27:49.280
Peanut butter and jelly?

27:49.282 --> 27:51.115
Yes, please.
[Giggles]

27:57.623 --> 28:01.559
- Why are you staring at me?
- I don't know. I like you.

28:04.463 --> 28:07.966
♪

28:08.336 --> 28:11.693
_

28:11.972 --> 28:13.638
Katy!

28:13.640 --> 28:16.307
What is wrong with you?

28:16.309 --> 28:21.212
♪

28:26.672 --> 28:28.105
Surprise!

28:28.107 --> 28:29.607
Hey, babe,
what are you doing here?

28:29.609 --> 28:31.475
Well, I realized that I've never
seen your place before,

28:31.477 --> 28:33.077
so I thought I would stop by...

28:33.079 --> 28:34.612
- and make you dinner.
- Mmm.

28:34.614 --> 28:36.280
I hope I'm not interrupting.

28:36.282 --> 28:38.082
Not at all.

28:38.084 --> 28:39.450
[Door closes]

28:39.452 --> 28:41.285
I'm gonna make my famous
<i>Chicken a la Marisol.</i>

28:41.287 --> 28:43.654
- Oh, yeah?
- You're gonna love it.

28:43.656 --> 28:45.289
- It has onions...
- Mmm!

28:45.291 --> 28:46.624
And peppers and...

28:46.626 --> 28:49.593
[Bag rustling]

28:49.595 --> 28:52.463
Oh, no!
I forgot the chicken.

28:52.465 --> 28:54.532
Well, that sounds like
a key ingredient.

28:54.534 --> 28:56.133
[Chuckles] [Chuckles]

28:56.135 --> 28:57.501
I can't believe it.

28:57.503 --> 28:59.437
Would you mind running out
and getting some?

28:59.439 --> 29:01.639
Sure. There's a supermarket
down the street.

29:01.641 --> 29:03.641
Oh, no.

29:03.643 --> 29:05.643
I need the organic,
free-range

29:05.645 --> 29:07.979
from the fancy market
near my place.

29:07.981 --> 29:09.714
Are you sure? It'll take
40 minutes, at least.

29:09.716 --> 29:13.317
Perfect. My sauce takes
a while to simmer.

29:13.319 --> 29:15.152
All right.

29:15.154 --> 29:16.554
Mmm.

29:16.556 --> 29:19.490
[Sighs]

29:19.492 --> 29:21.625
[Door closes]

29:21.627 --> 29:23.661
[Cap clatters]

29:25.530 --> 29:27.465
[Jar thuds]

29:27.467 --> 29:30.501
♪

29:37.542 --> 29:42.046
I'm so glad you could come over
tonight. [Chuckles]

29:42.048 --> 29:43.681
Isn't this relaxing?

29:43.683 --> 29:45.149
It is.
[Chuckles]

29:45.151 --> 29:47.018
I am so relaxed.

29:47.020 --> 29:48.486
[Chuckles]

29:48.488 --> 29:51.489
Oh, I know
what you're thinking.

29:51.491 --> 29:53.157
I doubt it.

29:53.159 --> 29:54.492
You're such a nice person.

29:54.494 --> 29:56.527
You don't wanna mess up
my marriage.

29:56.529 --> 29:58.029
That's it.

29:58.031 --> 29:59.697
Well, if it makes you feel
any better,

29:59.699 --> 30:01.332
we're not doing anything

30:01.334 --> 30:03.601
Sebastien hasn't done to me
already.

30:03.603 --> 30:05.102
What do you mean?

30:05.104 --> 30:07.204
Secret phone calls,
working late.

30:07.206 --> 30:09.073
I know he's having an affair.

30:13.211 --> 30:15.346
Let's not talk about
your husband.

30:15.348 --> 30:18.616
Exactly.
Tonight is about you and me.

30:18.618 --> 30:20.217
[Clink] [Chuckles]

30:20.219 --> 30:21.552
Mmm.

30:23.789 --> 30:25.756
Oh! [Chuckles]

30:25.758 --> 30:28.726
Well, hello there.

30:28.728 --> 30:31.395
Hi. [Giggles]
[Giggles]

30:31.397 --> 30:32.730
[Cell phone buzzes]

30:32.732 --> 30:34.131
[Chuckles]

30:34.133 --> 30:36.567
_

30:40.238 --> 30:42.139
I need more wine.

30:42.141 --> 30:43.541
You still have a full glass.

30:43.543 --> 30:45.743
[Chuckles nervously]

30:48.447 --> 30:49.747
Oh.

30:49.749 --> 30:51.482
[Shudders] Ooh!

30:51.484 --> 30:53.751
I'm a lush.
[Chuckles]

30:53.753 --> 30:55.252
Be right back.

30:55.254 --> 30:57.254
Uh...

30:58.824 --> 31:00.624
Katy pushed Miguel?

31:00.626 --> 31:02.726
He tried to kiss her.

31:02.728 --> 31:04.261
[Chuckles]

31:04.263 --> 31:07.298
Well, that sounds like
normal kid stuff.

31:07.300 --> 31:10.768
Then she said she would kill him
and dance in his blood.

31:10.770 --> 31:12.770
Oh.

31:12.772 --> 31:16.774
Mrs. Taylor, that is a very
scary thing for a girl to say.

31:16.776 --> 31:19.276
Where would she have
heard that?

31:19.278 --> 31:23.386
I...have no idea.

31:23.421 --> 31:26.350
- She had a hard childhood.
- In México?

31:26.352 --> 31:29.253
No. In Argentina.

31:29.255 --> 31:31.622
Katy told me the truth.

31:31.624 --> 31:33.290
Why are you lying about this?

31:33.292 --> 31:36.360
Rosie, it's none
of your business.

31:36.362 --> 31:37.661
She threatened my son.

31:37.663 --> 31:40.364
If Katy is dangerous,
then I need to know.

31:40.366 --> 31:42.500
No, no, she is not dangerous.

31:42.502 --> 31:45.136
Then why would she say
something like that?

31:46.771 --> 31:48.506
Before we adopted her,

31:48.508 --> 31:51.375
Katy witnessed
her father's murder.

31:51.377 --> 31:52.810
<i>Santo Dios.</i>

31:52.812 --> 31:56.814
And the men who killed him
told him they'd...

31:56.816 --> 31:58.616
dance in his blood.

31:58.618 --> 32:01.886
She was hiding in a closet.
She heard the whole thing.

32:01.888 --> 32:03.487
<i>Pobrecita.</i>

32:03.489 --> 32:07.191
So why can't you say
she's from México?

32:07.193 --> 32:08.792
Because she's a witness.

32:08.794 --> 32:11.695
And the men who killed
her father are looking for her.

32:11.697 --> 32:14.398
I know it is a lot to ask,

32:14.400 --> 32:17.368
but you have to keep
this secret.

32:17.370 --> 32:20.171
Did Blanca know about this?

32:20.173 --> 32:23.841
No, Michael and I are the only
ones who know the truth.

32:23.843 --> 32:25.843
And now me.

32:25.845 --> 32:27.645
And now you.

32:32.700 --> 32:34.012
_

32:34.047 --> 32:35.886
_
[Cell phone buzzes]

32:35.888 --> 32:38.355
You seem distracted.
[Glass thuds]

32:38.357 --> 32:41.358
Not at all.

32:41.360 --> 32:43.194
Do you mind
if we talk about work

32:43.196 --> 32:45.563
for the next 10, 12 minutes?

32:45.565 --> 32:47.598
Shh. It's okay.

32:47.600 --> 32:50.334
I'm new at this, too.

32:50.336 --> 32:52.770
- You are?
- Of course I am.

32:52.772 --> 32:56.607
I mean, I've... I've always
wanted to... mm, try this.

32:56.609 --> 32:59.710
[Chuckles] But it's always
felt so scary.

32:59.712 --> 33:02.346
So why now? [Chuckles]

33:02.348 --> 33:03.914
Because of you.

33:03.916 --> 33:06.684
Carmen, you're incredible.

33:06.686 --> 33:09.453
You're gorgeous and talented.

33:09.455 --> 33:11.722
But do you know what I like
the most about you?

33:11.724 --> 33:13.557
Is it my hair?

33:13.559 --> 33:14.858
Because I get a lot of
compliments about my hair.

33:14.860 --> 33:18.729
[Laughing] No. No.

33:18.731 --> 33:22.399
I love how honest you are.

33:22.401 --> 33:25.436
You always tell it like it is.

33:25.438 --> 33:29.940
It makes me feel like
I can be honest, too.

33:35.780 --> 33:37.715
I can't do it.

33:37.717 --> 33:39.583
Are... are you sure?

33:42.454 --> 33:45.823
You're great,
and I am so flattered,

33:45.825 --> 33:49.426
but it... it feels...
it feels wrong.

33:49.428 --> 33:51.662
Yeah, oh, you're...
you're not into it.

33:51.664 --> 33:53.297
I'm so sorry.

33:53.299 --> 33:54.632
[Sighs]

33:54.634 --> 33:56.800
Are you okay with us
keeping it professional?

33:56.802 --> 33:58.402
Of course.

33:58.404 --> 33:59.970
Okay.

34:04.976 --> 34:07.611
Jacklyn...

34:07.613 --> 34:10.281
you deserve to be happy.

34:10.283 --> 34:12.283
What does that mean?

34:12.284 --> 34:14.518
It means you shouldn't deny
who you are.

34:14.520 --> 34:16.987
And if your marriage is not
making you happy,

34:16.989 --> 34:20.324
I think you should...
just end it.

34:30.235 --> 34:34.071
Hey, I just wanna say
I'm sorry.

34:34.072 --> 34:35.839
They should've told you
about me.

34:35.841 --> 34:37.174
It's not your fault.

34:37.176 --> 34:40.210
They put us both
in an awkward position.

34:40.212 --> 34:42.746
But... [Sighs]
I am starting to think

34:42.748 --> 34:45.047
this arrangement might be
a good idea.

34:45.050 --> 34:46.917
Really?
[Sighs]

34:46.918 --> 34:50.687
I can't handle this house
all alone right now.

34:50.688 --> 34:52.688
I could really use some help.

34:52.690 --> 34:53.924
Of course.

34:53.926 --> 34:55.859
Here, I just finished sweeping,

34:55.860 --> 34:59.830
but I can't get down on
the floor to scoop up the dirt.

34:59.832 --> 35:01.098
Would you mind?

35:01.100 --> 35:03.200
Not at all.

35:07.038 --> 35:08.772
What are you doing?

35:08.774 --> 35:10.073
Sweeping.

35:10.075 --> 35:11.775
I just did that part.

35:11.777 --> 35:15.212
I know, but I'll just
sweep again to be safe.

35:15.214 --> 35:16.713
[Chuckles]

35:18.716 --> 35:22.085
[Hangers clack]

35:42.640 --> 35:46.610
♪

35:46.612 --> 35:48.011
What are you doing?

35:54.481 --> 35:57.483
Marisol, why are you pointing
my gun at me?

35:57.485 --> 36:00.118
Why do you have a gun?

36:00.120 --> 36:02.988
After I found the hand,
I was feeling a little nervous,

36:02.990 --> 36:07.559
so I bought a gun to protect
myself and my girlfriend.

36:07.561 --> 36:09.127
And besides,
I was in the military

36:09.129 --> 36:10.329
and I know how to handle a gun.

36:10.331 --> 36:13.398
You, on the other hand, do not.

36:13.400 --> 36:16.969
What about Louie Becker?
At the country club?

36:16.971 --> 36:19.538
- Is that what this is about?
- Just tell me the truth.

36:19.540 --> 36:22.007
Louie was a pig.

36:22.009 --> 36:24.009
Okay, I caught him getting
handsy with some women

36:24.011 --> 36:25.577
at the club,
and I called him out on it.

36:25.579 --> 36:29.348
So he made up some lies
about me and got me fired.

36:29.350 --> 36:32.317
Why didn't you tell me?

36:32.319 --> 36:34.987
Because it was embarrassing.

36:34.989 --> 36:36.355
I was trying to forget
about it.

36:36.357 --> 36:41.260
Now can you please
put the gun down?

36:41.262 --> 36:42.528
Is this why
you came over tonight,

36:42.530 --> 36:45.197
to go through my things?

36:45.199 --> 36:48.333
It's just, when I heard about
your incident with Louie Becker,

36:48.335 --> 36:50.369
my imagination just ran
a little wild.

36:50.371 --> 36:52.037
You thought I killed him?

36:52.039 --> 36:55.507
I...thought maybe something
happened to you in the war,

36:55.509 --> 36:58.410
and you might have PTSD?

36:58.412 --> 37:01.547
No, you have PTSD from all
the bad guys you've been with.

37:01.549 --> 37:04.883
Your exes have made you crazy.

37:04.885 --> 37:08.587
Okay, I overreacted.

37:08.589 --> 37:11.356
- Can we talk about this?
- I think you should go.

37:21.100 --> 37:23.235
Hey. You're alone.

37:23.237 --> 37:26.138
I thought you were meeting
one of your artists tonight.

37:26.140 --> 37:27.439
She left.

37:27.441 --> 37:29.308
Oh. So soon?

37:29.310 --> 37:33.412
Sit down. We need to talk.

37:33.414 --> 37:35.914
In a minute.
I need to make a quick call.

37:35.916 --> 37:38.617
Sebastien, please.

37:38.619 --> 37:40.085
[Sighs heavily]

37:40.087 --> 37:43.488
Come on, Carmen, pick up.

37:43.490 --> 37:46.224
[Cell phone rings]

37:46.226 --> 37:49.227
[Ring]

37:49.229 --> 37:50.929
[Glass clatters]

37:50.931 --> 37:55.931
[Ring]

37:57.171 --> 38:01.039
[Ring]

38:02.942 --> 38:07.012
Deion, what do you think
of the camembert?

38:07.014 --> 38:10.148
It's like the brie, but smelly.

38:10.150 --> 38:13.018
We pay extra for the smell.

38:13.020 --> 38:17.022
You have
a very refined palette.

38:17.024 --> 38:18.657
Thank you, Mrs. Powell.

38:18.659 --> 38:22.194
You know, you don't have to
call me "Mrs. Powell."

38:22.196 --> 38:24.696
Why don't you call me "Mom"?

38:24.698 --> 38:27.032
Okay, Mom.

38:27.034 --> 38:28.567
[Chuckles]

38:42.148 --> 38:45.984
Mr. Dresden? Adrian Powell.

38:45.986 --> 38:49.154
How's the P.I. business?

38:49.156 --> 38:50.989
Good. Good, good, good.

38:50.991 --> 38:54.059
Listen, I have a job for you.

38:54.161 --> 38:59.064
I need you to find
a young boy's birth parents.

39:01.334 --> 39:03.374
Michael,
I'm glad you stopped by.

39:04.109 --> 39:06.302
Well, I know how much
you care about Taylor,

39:06.357 --> 39:09.474
and I thought maybe you could,
you know, help me out.

39:09.476 --> 39:12.545
- What can I do?
- Just keep an eye on her,

39:12.647 --> 39:14.847
make sure she's all right.

39:14.849 --> 39:18.517
I'm afraid she's...
she's in over her head.

39:18.519 --> 39:21.253
- How so?
- Honestly, I don't know.

39:21.255 --> 39:24.256
Michael, when you have
something good,

39:24.258 --> 39:27.026
you shouldn't just
throw it away.

39:27.028 --> 39:28.694
Believe me, I know.

39:28.696 --> 39:30.129
It's not that simple.

39:30.131 --> 39:31.931
Will someone at least tell me
what this is about?

39:31.933 --> 39:35.868
Money? Parenting?
Infidelity?

39:36.070 --> 39:38.404
Well, not on my part.

39:38.406 --> 39:39.872
Excuse me?

39:39.874 --> 39:41.240
She's having an affair.

39:41.242 --> 39:43.809
I think it's been
going on for months.

39:43.811 --> 39:45.944
You think she's been
cheating on you?

39:45.946 --> 39:47.746
With who?

39:47.748 --> 39:51.049
You'll have to ask her.

39:51.051 --> 39:52.418
[Knock on door]

39:53.987 --> 39:55.821
Rosie. I wasn't expecting you.

39:55.823 --> 39:57.322
I need to talk to you.

39:57.324 --> 40:00.058
Uh, you know, it's not really
a good time right now.

40:00.060 --> 40:01.427
Did you tell Miguel
to kiss a girl?

40:01.429 --> 40:02.928
What?

40:02.930 --> 40:05.264
He said he was following
your advice.

40:05.266 --> 40:07.232
No, that...
that's not what I told him.

40:07.234 --> 40:08.767
But, hey, way to go, Miguel.

40:08.769 --> 40:11.770
No! It was not
a way to go.

40:11.772 --> 40:14.907
Spence, I was counting on you
to handle this.

40:14.909 --> 40:18.777
If Ernesto had been here,
this never would have happened.

40:18.779 --> 40:20.913
Well, I guess Ernesto's not only
a better husband than I am,

40:20.915 --> 40:22.915
he's a better father, too, huh?

40:22.917 --> 40:25.451
What is that supposed to mean?

40:25.453 --> 40:29.321
You crushed me, Rosie.

40:29.323 --> 40:30.956
When you left me for him,

40:30.958 --> 40:33.125
you ripped my heart
out of my chest.

40:33.127 --> 40:35.794
- Spence...
- I gave up my marriage for you.

40:35.796 --> 40:37.930
I lost my son.

40:37.932 --> 40:41.166
I stood by you while you were
in a coma for months,

40:41.168 --> 40:43.869
and never once
did I give up on you.

40:43.871 --> 40:45.337
The minute he comes back
into your life,

40:45.339 --> 40:46.839
you give up on me.

40:46.841 --> 40:49.374
I'm... I'm sorry.

40:49.376 --> 40:51.109
You know what the worst part
about it is?

40:51.111 --> 40:53.479
I still love you.

40:55.048 --> 40:58.884
So, you know, guess what?
I am not okay. I'm a wreck.

40:58.886 --> 41:01.920
[Whispers] I should go.

41:10.830 --> 41:12.164
[Sighs]

41:18.838 --> 41:20.372
She's gone.

41:20.374 --> 41:22.374
[Sighs] Do you think
she knows about us?

41:22.376 --> 41:24.343
No.

41:24.345 --> 41:26.578
She has no idea.

41:26.580 --> 41:29.581
♪

